1. Country_ Country in the data set. The countries included are:
3. Year_ Years covered in the data set. The data set covers for some countries the 1963-2009 period.
4. Quality_ Quality rating of the country data in the PWT.
7. Fertility_  Total fertility rate per woman.
10. X_ Real Gross Domestic Product in 2005 purchasing power parity (Chain Index).
11. K_ Our estimated net fixed standardized capital stock in 2005 purchasing power parity
12. D_ Estimated depreciation from our net fixed standardized capital stock in 2005 purchasing power parity
14. d_ Estimated depreciation per worker in 2005 purchasing power parity
15. k_ Capital-labor ratio in 2005 purchasing power parity
16. x_ Labor productivity expressed in real GDP in 2000 purchasing power parity per worker in 2005 purchasing power parity
18. x(fc) _ Labor productivity corrected for the business cycle in 2005 purchasing power parity.
19. rho(fc)_ Productivity of capital corrected for the business cycle.
20. ws_ Wage share in the GDP.
21. w_ Average real wage in 2005 purchasing power parity.
23. i_ Investment per worker-year in 2005 purchasing power parity
24. c_ Social consumption per worker-year in 2005 purchasing power parity
25. gX(%)_ Growth rate of GDP calculated between the year t and the year t-5
26. chi(%)_ Growth rate of capital productivity calculated between the year t and the year t-5.
27. gamma(%)_ Growth rate of labor productivity calculated between the year t and the year t-5.
29. a _ The ratio between CO2 emissions and our capital stock, it is expressed in Kg CO2/$ 2005 PPP.
30. o _ The ratio between CO2 emissions and GDP. It is also expressed in Kg CO2/$ 2005 PPP.
31. b _ The ratio between  CO2 emissions and the number of workers, It is also expressed in Kg CO2/worker.
